In this article, it is mentioned that the President of the United States had a phone call with the Managing Director of the International Monetary Fund (IMF), Christine Lagarde. The call was to discuss the global economic situation and recent developments in financial markets. They also discussed the importance of close cooperation between the United States and the IMF. The President congratulated Lagarde on her appointment as Managing Director and emphasized the need for policies that promote growth and job creation, while also ensuring fiscal consolidation in the medium term. They both agreed on the importance of rebalancing global demand towards emerging markets.